1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:01,350
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,350 --> 00:00:02,683
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,850 --> 00:00:05,983
(Episode 59)

4
00:00:06,683 --> 00:00:08,783
Please, Ji Seon.

5
00:00:10,450 --> 00:00:11,583
Please don't go.

6
00:00:12,350 --> 00:00:14,050
A child abandoned by her mother...

7
00:00:14,050 --> 00:00:17,050
is as good as dead
for the rest of her life.

8
00:00:17,683 --> 00:00:19,883
If even the mother
who gave birth to her abandons her,

9
00:00:20,050 --> 00:00:21,250
where can she go,

10
00:00:21,250 --> 00:00:23,650
and how can she ever put down roots?

11
00:00:24,983 --> 00:00:28,150
Mother, I'm really late. I have to go.

12
00:00:28,950 --> 00:00:31,250
Ji Seon. Bit Na's mom!

13
00:00:33,750 --> 00:00:35,150
What do I do?

14
00:00:42,683 --> 00:00:45,483
Ma'am, when did you get here?

15
00:00:46,583 --> 00:00:47,583
Just a little while ago.

16
00:00:48,083 --> 00:00:50,750
I came to drop that off.

17
00:00:52,150 --> 00:00:53,250
You didn't have to bring all this.

18
00:00:54,250 --> 00:00:55,650
Please come inside.

19
00:00:55,650 --> 00:00:56,650
No.

20
00:00:57,050 --> 00:00:59,550
You seem quite troubled,
so I should get going.

21
00:00:59,750 --> 00:01:00,750
No, please.

22
00:01:01,750 --> 00:01:02,983
Come in for a moment.

23
00:01:05,150 --> 00:01:06,150
I...

24
00:01:07,183 --> 00:01:09,650
just need someone to talk to.

25
00:01:12,650 --> 00:01:13,883
(Agreement on Child Custody
and Parental Rights)

26
00:01:13,883 --> 00:01:15,350
She's my former daughter-in-law.

27
00:01:16,583 --> 00:01:18,950
She divorced my son not long ago.

28
00:01:20,383 --> 00:01:22,450
I have a seven-year-old granddaughter.

29
00:01:23,283 --> 00:01:25,183
For the child's sake,

30
00:01:25,183 --> 00:01:27,650
I've been trying to get them back together
somehow, but it isn't easy.

31
00:01:27,650 --> 00:01:30,383
I see. That's what happened.

32
00:01:30,550 --> 00:01:31,550
Ma'am.

33
00:01:32,850 --> 00:01:34,550
What should I do in a situation like this?

34
00:01:36,183 --> 00:01:39,483
Even if the dad has to raise the child
for now because she's struggling,

35
00:01:40,350 --> 00:01:42,650
she didn't even see her child
despite coming all the way here.

36
00:01:43,150 --> 00:01:46,350
How can she give up her own child
so easily?

37
00:01:47,450 --> 00:01:49,650
A parent, a mother,

38
00:01:50,183 --> 00:01:52,150
should never do that, right?

39
00:01:52,783 --> 00:01:54,783
No, she shouldn't. Never.

40
00:01:56,550 --> 00:02:00,050
But perhaps she's not trying
to give up her child,

41
00:02:00,650 --> 00:02:02,550
and circumstances beyond her control...

42
00:02:03,150 --> 00:02:05,583
have left her no choice.

43
00:02:05,650 --> 00:02:07,050
Circumstances beyond her control?

44
00:02:07,850 --> 00:02:09,250
What circumstances
could possibly be that serious?

45
00:02:09,850 --> 00:02:12,350
Unless there's a war
or a natural disaster,

46
00:02:12,683 --> 00:02:14,583
what parent in the world...

47
00:02:15,750 --> 00:02:17,550
I was only trying to comfort you.

48
00:02:18,450 --> 00:02:22,183
Anyway, your daughter-in-law...

49
00:02:22,250 --> 00:02:24,750
must be living in hell right now too.

50
00:02:25,683 --> 00:02:26,683
I suppose she is.

51
00:02:27,850 --> 00:02:29,583
Otherwise, she wouldn't be a mother.

52
00:02:31,650 --> 00:02:34,483
By the way, your parents...

53
00:02:36,350 --> 00:02:37,450
My parents?

54
00:02:39,350 --> 00:02:40,350
I don't have any.

55
00:02:42,350 --> 00:02:45,950
My father passed away before I was born,
so I never knew him.

56
00:02:47,550 --> 00:02:48,550
And my mother...

57
00:02:51,050 --> 00:02:52,783
She passed away a long time ago too.

58
00:02:54,250 --> 00:02:57,250
I'm sorry. I shouldn't have asked.

59
00:02:57,883 --> 00:02:58,883
It's okay.

60
00:03:00,283 --> 00:03:02,683
Strangely, whenever I'm with you,

61
00:03:03,250 --> 00:03:05,350
I find myself opening up
without even realizing it.

62
00:03:07,350 --> 00:03:10,350
By the way, you've brought so much.

63
00:03:11,050 --> 00:03:14,983
They're chicken soup and flower pancakes.
I hope you like them.

64
00:03:17,450 --> 00:03:18,450
Flower pancakes?

65
00:03:18,650 --> 00:03:21,383
Yes. When I was younger,

66
00:03:22,383 --> 00:03:24,650
I used to go up the mountain
behind the village, pick azaleas,

67
00:03:24,650 --> 00:03:26,950
and make flower pancakes.

68
00:03:28,950 --> 00:03:32,750
My daughter loved them.

69
00:03:35,050 --> 00:03:38,050
Thinking of the old days,
I decided to make some.

70
00:03:38,550 --> 00:03:40,050
You have a daughter?

71
00:03:41,750 --> 00:03:44,383
A daughter with a mother...

72
00:03:44,383 --> 00:03:47,783
as warm and kind as you
must be very lucky.

73
00:03:48,583 --> 00:03:50,350
I should get going now.

74
00:03:50,650 --> 00:03:54,283
You always bring things over like this,

75
00:03:54,283 --> 00:03:56,250
and I never even get the chance
to treat you to a meal.

76
00:03:56,750 --> 00:03:58,250
Thank you for the tea.

77
00:04:01,250 --> 00:04:02,450
You don't need to come out.

78
00:04:02,450 --> 00:04:04,850
You've got enough on your mind already.
Please stay inside.

79
00:04:05,983 --> 00:04:08,550
All right. Take care.

80
00:04:08,550 --> 00:04:09,550
Okay.

81
00:04:41,383 --> 00:04:43,350
Excuse me.

82
00:04:43,883 --> 00:04:46,450
If you don't mind me asking,
how old are you this year?

83
00:04:47,650 --> 00:04:50,583
How old? Are you asking my age right now?

84
00:04:51,083 --> 00:04:53,250
Don't you know it's rude
to ask something like that?

85
00:04:53,850 --> 00:04:56,150
Well, it's only rude
when you're asking a young person.

86
00:04:56,850 --> 00:04:59,050
How could it be rude at your age?

87
00:04:59,783 --> 00:05:02,550
What's that supposed to mean?

88
00:05:02,983 --> 00:05:06,250
Why are you getting so upset
over a simple question?

89
00:05:06,250 --> 00:05:09,150
Did you help me get older?

90
00:05:09,683 --> 00:05:11,850
And if you're going to ask,

91
00:05:11,850 --> 00:05:13,950
you should tell me your age first.

92
00:05:14,350 --> 00:05:15,883
Then ask.

93
00:05:17,350 --> 00:05:19,783
I was born in 1958, the Year of the Dog.

94
00:05:20,350 --> 00:05:21,750
I'm 69.

95
00:05:22,450 --> 00:05:25,183
Really? I didn't think you were that old.

96
00:05:26,383 --> 00:05:28,450
You've had your fair share of years too.

97
00:05:29,550 --> 00:05:32,850
I was born in 1953, the Year of the Snake.

98
00:05:33,350 --> 00:05:34,350
I'm 73.

99
00:05:34,450 --> 00:05:35,450
What?

100
00:05:36,750 --> 00:05:38,850
You're much older than me.

101
00:05:39,550 --> 00:05:41,550
Let's go, Mr. Ju.

102
00:05:43,250 --> 00:05:45,483
Why are you back already?

103
00:05:45,683 --> 00:05:47,783
I thought you'd stay and chat for a while.

104
00:05:48,083 --> 00:05:50,983
- Goodbye.
- Come by again sometime.

105
00:05:51,650 --> 00:05:53,283
Wait for me, Madam!

106
00:05:54,750 --> 00:05:55,750
Big sis,

107
00:05:56,783 --> 00:05:57,783
see you next time.

108
00:06:00,150 --> 00:06:01,283
"Big sis?"

109
00:06:01,883 --> 00:06:05,750
He's only seen me a few times,
and he's already calling me that? Rascal!

110
00:06:07,950 --> 00:06:09,250
I'm home.

111
00:06:09,750 --> 00:06:13,350
Hey, Bit Na.
Did you have a good day at kindergarten?

112
00:06:13,350 --> 00:06:16,250
Yes. Auntie, I want to go see Grandma.

113
00:06:16,883 --> 00:06:18,450
Wait a minute.

114
00:06:18,450 --> 00:06:21,350
Bit Na, stay and play a little longer.

115
00:06:21,950 --> 00:06:23,150
Yeah, Bit Na.

116
00:06:23,250 --> 00:06:25,150
Should we go outside
and play hopscotch one more time?

117
00:06:25,350 --> 00:06:27,250
We already played five times
on the way here.

118
00:06:27,650 --> 00:06:29,083
I'm tired.

119
00:06:30,350 --> 00:06:31,383
Bit Na.

120
00:06:31,383 --> 00:06:32,950
Grandma!

121
00:06:34,250 --> 00:06:35,550
Did she come? What did she say?

122
00:06:36,450 --> 00:06:37,850
Maybe later.

123
00:06:38,550 --> 00:06:39,950
Bit Na, let's go home.

124
00:06:39,950 --> 00:06:40,950
Okay, Grandma.

125
00:06:41,383 --> 00:06:42,750
Thanks, Cho Rong.

126
00:06:43,250 --> 00:06:44,250
Let's go.

127
00:06:44,383 --> 00:06:45,650
Bye-bye.

128
00:06:45,850 --> 00:06:48,050
Bye-bye.

129
00:06:48,383 --> 00:06:50,250
She's exactly like her mom.

130
00:06:50,250 --> 00:06:52,550
She always has an answer for everything.

131
00:06:52,850 --> 00:06:54,350
She didn't even open the envelope.

132
00:06:54,950 --> 00:06:56,750
She told me I watch too many dramas.

133
00:06:58,883 --> 00:07:00,250
She wasn't entirely wrong.

134
00:07:00,250 --> 00:07:02,050
If you watch dramas,

135
00:07:02,050 --> 00:07:03,550
you see scenes like that all the time.

136
00:07:03,850 --> 00:07:05,083
Someone shoves over an envelope and says,

137
00:07:05,983 --> 00:07:07,050
"Take this and leave."

138
00:07:07,450 --> 00:07:08,850
Are you kidding me?

139
00:07:09,450 --> 00:07:11,350
When I told her there was one in there,

140
00:07:11,350 --> 00:07:14,283
she said maybe if there were a hundred.
One wasn't even worth looking at.

141
00:07:14,450 --> 00:07:15,550
The nerve of that girl.

142
00:07:16,750 --> 00:07:18,883
She's unbelievably arrogant.

143
00:07:20,183 --> 00:07:22,650
Wait a minute.
Does raising your daughter wrong...

144
00:07:22,650 --> 00:07:24,850
count as grounds for resignation?

145
00:07:24,850 --> 00:07:27,283
Hold on.
Which category should this go under?

146
00:07:28,250 --> 00:07:29,550
What is it? Let me see.

147
00:07:30,750 --> 00:07:31,750
What's this?

148
00:07:33,550 --> 00:07:36,383
You're trying to fire Mr. Cho with this?

149
00:07:36,850 --> 00:07:38,750
Forget this.

150
00:07:38,750 --> 00:07:40,683
You need something
that really packs a punch.

151
00:07:41,650 --> 00:07:43,183
A punch? Like what?

152
00:07:43,183 --> 00:07:46,850
What about setting a trap
and catching him embezzling,

153
00:07:47,150 --> 00:07:50,883
or taking illegal money or something?

154
00:07:51,150 --> 00:07:53,550
Forget it. He'd never fall for that.
If he were that kind of person,

155
00:07:53,550 --> 00:07:57,350
would I be sitting here
writing petty lists like this?

156
00:07:57,750 --> 00:08:00,250
He's so rigid.

157
00:08:00,483 --> 00:08:02,783
I offered him a much higher salary,

158
00:08:03,183 --> 00:08:05,983
and he insisted on being paid the same
as the veteran assistants.

159
00:08:05,983 --> 00:08:08,450
He actually negotiated
his own salary down.

160
00:08:09,383 --> 00:08:10,383
He's that bad?

161
00:08:10,950 --> 00:08:14,050
Anyway,
make sure you talk some sense into Min Ho.

162
00:08:14,383 --> 00:08:15,883
We're already on the verge
of splitting everything.

163
00:08:16,350 --> 00:08:19,683
If he loses to Gyeol
in the competition too, we're doomed.

164
00:08:19,683 --> 00:08:22,150
That's an awful thing to say.

165
00:08:23,050 --> 00:08:25,450
The victory has to be Min Ho's
this time too.

166
00:08:25,550 --> 00:08:26,550
Honey!

167
00:08:27,250 --> 00:08:29,350
Don't even mention victory.

168
00:08:29,583 --> 00:08:31,050
It reminds me of Seung Ri
and irritates me!

169
00:08:32,383 --> 00:08:35,383
Crystal, the more I think about it...

170
00:08:35,950 --> 00:08:36,950
That's it.

171
00:08:37,183 --> 00:08:40,250
Let's make Manager Seo
our daughter-in-law.

172
00:08:40,850 --> 00:08:42,450
What? Have you gone mad?

173
00:08:43,150 --> 00:08:45,083
Give them our Min Ho? Seriously?

174
00:08:45,283 --> 00:08:47,083
Why would you pair him with her?

175
00:08:49,050 --> 00:08:51,250
Think about it.

176
00:08:51,583 --> 00:08:53,483
It's not like Min Ho is our only son.

177
00:08:54,250 --> 00:08:55,250
What?

178
00:08:55,283 --> 00:08:58,050
We've almost finished integrating
Joy's lifestyle data.

179
00:08:58,050 --> 00:09:00,883
Good. At this point,
Joy's integration is nearly complete.

180
00:09:01,350 --> 00:09:03,183
I've arranged it
so that the remote Tapgol Park area...

181
00:09:03,183 --> 00:09:05,550
connects as naturally as possible
with the other spaces.

182
00:09:06,250 --> 00:09:08,150
Thanks to both of you,
everything's moving smoothly again.

183
00:09:08,783 --> 00:09:11,750
Then I'll head to the archive room
for some materials.

184
00:09:12,783 --> 00:09:13,783
Okay.

185
00:09:19,950 --> 00:09:21,950
Who did you meet before the meeting?

186
00:09:22,183 --> 00:09:24,750
Sorry? A friend.

187
00:09:25,550 --> 00:09:27,950
A friend? Was Cho Rong here?

188
00:09:28,050 --> 00:09:29,850
Then you should've invited me too.

189
00:09:30,383 --> 00:09:32,850
Do you think Cho Rong is my only friend?

190
00:09:35,850 --> 00:09:37,050
What are you doing tonight?

191
00:09:37,450 --> 00:09:38,483
Tonight?

192
00:09:38,883 --> 00:09:41,283
I'll wash up and go to sleep. What else?

193
00:09:43,050 --> 00:09:45,383
Then let's meet in the yard at 10 p.m.

194
00:09:45,650 --> 00:09:48,950
What?
What will we do in the yard at that hour?

195
00:09:50,550 --> 00:09:52,183
Why hasn't there been any progress lately?

196
00:09:53,150 --> 00:09:54,850
After I reported too hastily last time,

197
00:09:55,150 --> 00:09:58,450
I disappointed Madam greatly,
so I've been proceeding carefully.

198
00:09:59,383 --> 00:10:03,083
We're checking everything one by one,
including burn scars...

199
00:10:03,450 --> 00:10:04,650
and records of scar removal procedures.

200
00:10:06,383 --> 00:10:07,383
I see.

201
00:10:07,950 --> 00:10:11,283
What about finding the owner of the diner?
How's that going?

202
00:10:14,750 --> 00:10:15,950
I'm looking, but not much has come up yet.

203
00:10:17,350 --> 00:10:20,450
After sending the child to the orphanage,

204
00:10:21,083 --> 00:10:22,150
the diner owner likely
cut off all contact,

205
00:10:22,650 --> 00:10:24,750
so even if we find him,
he probably won't be much help.

206
00:10:24,750 --> 00:10:27,383
What are you talking about?
How can you be so sure?

207
00:10:28,283 --> 00:10:30,650
He may have been contacted
after the adoption was annulled,

208
00:10:30,983 --> 00:10:32,983
or he might provide another clue.

209
00:10:34,150 --> 00:10:36,850
Don't jump to conclusions. Keep digging.

210
00:10:37,950 --> 00:10:39,950
Yes, sir.

211
00:10:53,283 --> 00:10:54,283
I'm home, Father.

212
00:10:54,950 --> 00:10:56,950
Hey. You're home early.

213
00:10:58,250 --> 00:10:59,283
You may leave now.

214
00:10:59,950 --> 00:11:01,850
- Let's go inside.
- No, please go ahead.

215
00:11:02,850 --> 00:11:04,150
I need a word with Mr. Seo.

216
00:11:04,150 --> 00:11:05,750
Really? All right then.

217
00:11:06,550 --> 00:11:07,550
Have a good evening, Chairman.

218
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:15,650
So? Any progress?

219
00:11:16,350 --> 00:11:17,783
Progress on what?

220
00:11:18,150 --> 00:11:20,050
Finding my sister.

221
00:11:20,750 --> 00:11:23,350
Things have been awfully quiet
since the last false lead.

222
00:11:24,550 --> 00:11:25,550
Nothing yet.

223
00:11:26,650 --> 00:11:28,750
Of course not.

224
00:11:30,050 --> 00:11:31,150
What are you going to do about Seung Ri?

225
00:11:33,583 --> 00:11:35,650
Seung Ri is completely hung up on Gyeol.

226
00:11:36,250 --> 00:11:39,150
What if we all join forces
and give them a push?

227
00:11:39,650 --> 00:11:42,050
Do you really think that's something
we can make happen?

228
00:11:42,050 --> 00:11:45,050
The agreement between the two of them
is what matters most,

229
00:11:45,250 --> 00:11:48,350
but wouldn't things be different
if the adults stepped in?

230
00:11:49,383 --> 00:11:51,750
Honestly, the best outcome would be
for the kids to head off...

231
00:11:51,750 --> 00:11:53,150
to America after the competition.

232
00:11:53,250 --> 00:11:57,050
If Gyeol and Seung Ri work out,
we'll end up becoming in-laws.

233
00:11:58,350 --> 00:11:59,650
Seems like you're okay with that.

234
00:11:59,950 --> 00:12:01,150
You already know the answer.

235
00:12:01,950 --> 00:12:03,250
Anyway, think it over carefully.

236
00:12:04,150 --> 00:12:07,350
As long as it isn't Min Ho,
I'm perfectly fine with Seung Ri.

237
00:12:08,150 --> 00:12:09,183
I'll be going now.

238
00:12:16,950 --> 00:12:17,950
Seo Gwon Sik.

239
00:12:19,150 --> 00:12:21,250
He doesn't even realize Mother's daughter
is right under his nose.

240
00:12:22,750 --> 00:12:24,250
Before a fool like you figures it out,

241
00:12:25,150 --> 00:12:27,283
I'll make sure you never find her,
whatever it takes.

242
00:12:36,650 --> 00:12:38,450
What's wrong? Are you feeling sick?

243
00:12:39,250 --> 00:12:42,550
You've looked down ever since
you came back from Mr. Cho's house.

244
00:12:43,250 --> 00:12:45,950
No. I'm just a little tired.

245
00:12:46,650 --> 00:12:48,983
Mr. Seo stopped by earlier.

246
00:12:50,650 --> 00:12:53,350
He's been giving it a lot of thought
because of what happened last time.

247
00:12:54,250 --> 00:12:57,783
He's even checking for burn scars
one by one.

248
00:12:58,583 --> 00:13:00,683
He's a truly good man.

249
00:13:01,750 --> 00:13:05,550
Not many people stay that loyal
for decades.

250
00:13:06,150 --> 00:13:08,050
You're right.

251
00:13:08,950 --> 00:13:11,683
By the way, did you register
for the people-finder app?

252
00:13:12,083 --> 00:13:13,683
Not yet.

253
00:13:13,783 --> 00:13:16,650
Is it harder than you thought to post it?

254
00:13:17,283 --> 00:13:18,350
Want me to do it for you?

255
00:13:18,350 --> 00:13:19,350
No.

256
00:13:19,883 --> 00:13:23,750
You should get some rest.
Dinner will be ready soon.

257
00:13:24,550 --> 00:13:25,583
Just rest a little longer.

258
00:13:26,250 --> 00:13:27,783
We have a housekeeper
and a daughter-in-law.

259
00:13:28,350 --> 00:13:31,350
Why do you insist
on preparing all three meals yourself?

260
00:13:31,483 --> 00:13:35,983
I can never leave your meals
to someone else.

261
00:13:36,450 --> 00:13:37,550
You know that.

262
00:13:39,250 --> 00:13:42,950
Maybe it's the flower pancakes,
but I'm not hungry.

263
00:13:43,383 --> 00:13:44,383
Get some more rest.

264
00:13:45,050 --> 00:13:46,083
How pretty.

265
00:13:46,450 --> 00:13:48,250
Grandma, what's this called?

266
00:13:50,350 --> 00:13:51,850
These are flower pancakes.

267
00:13:52,150 --> 00:13:54,683
They're called that because flowers
are pressed into them before cooking.

268
00:13:55,650 --> 00:13:57,250
There are flowers you can eat?

269
00:14:01,150 --> 00:14:02,550
It's good, Grandma.

270
00:14:02,650 --> 00:14:04,850
Good. Eat plenty, Bit Na.

271
00:14:05,550 --> 00:14:07,983
Team Manager Ko's grandmother
made all of these?

272
00:14:08,183 --> 00:14:10,083
I know. These take so much work.

273
00:14:10,083 --> 00:14:11,850
She really went to all that trouble
for our family.

274
00:14:12,583 --> 00:14:14,950
Please thank her for me.

275
00:14:15,450 --> 00:14:16,650
Yes, Mother.

276
00:14:18,850 --> 00:14:20,250
Mother?

277
00:14:22,450 --> 00:14:24,550
Since you're Eun Ae's mother...

278
00:14:25,550 --> 00:14:27,850
Mom, just let him call you that.

279
00:14:27,983 --> 00:14:29,983
Cho Rong calls you "Mother" too.

280
00:14:30,950 --> 00:14:33,750
Fine. I didn't say anything. Now eat.

281
00:14:34,950 --> 00:14:35,950
You're not eating?

282
00:14:36,350 --> 00:14:37,983
I'm not really hungry.

283
00:14:39,150 --> 00:14:40,483
Bit Na, eat plenty.

284
00:14:40,650 --> 00:14:42,283
- Yes, Grandma.
- Good.

285
00:14:43,550 --> 00:14:44,750
Is she sick?

286
00:14:45,450 --> 00:14:46,450
Let's eat.

287
00:14:46,983 --> 00:14:48,250
Team Manager Ko, you should eat.

288
00:14:48,350 --> 00:14:50,050
Yes. Enjoy your meal.

289
00:15:06,150 --> 00:15:07,850
Is it because of the flower pancakes?

290
00:15:08,150 --> 00:15:09,150
What?

291
00:15:09,150 --> 00:15:13,383
You said you loved the flower pancakes
your mom used to make.

292
00:15:14,383 --> 00:15:16,150
Yeah, I did.

293
00:15:17,650 --> 00:15:19,450
They were the most delicious food...

294
00:15:20,150 --> 00:15:21,750
in the world to me.

295
00:15:23,783 --> 00:15:27,850
One time, on Children's Day, they served
flower pancakes at the orphanage.

296
00:15:28,950 --> 00:15:30,650
I took one bite and threw it all up.

297
00:15:31,550 --> 00:15:33,783
After that, I couldn't eat them at all.

298
00:15:35,450 --> 00:15:36,750
My body rejected them.

299
00:15:38,850 --> 00:15:40,083
It rejected all the foods...

300
00:15:41,350 --> 00:15:43,383
that person used to make for me
when I was little.

301
00:15:46,850 --> 00:15:50,383
But now, it's all faded.
It's already been 50 years.

302
00:15:51,783 --> 00:15:54,983
If it's all faded,
why aren't you eating dinner with us?

303
00:15:56,550 --> 00:15:58,850
Do you have something else on your mind?

304
00:16:01,283 --> 00:16:03,450
Bit Na's mom came by today.

305
00:16:04,183 --> 00:16:05,183
What?

306
00:16:05,850 --> 00:16:06,850
What did she say?

307
00:16:07,150 --> 00:16:08,483
Did she see Bit Na?

308
00:16:08,483 --> 00:16:09,483
No.

309
00:16:10,583 --> 00:16:13,383
She stopped by on her way to work
and left because she didn't have time.

310
00:16:15,250 --> 00:16:16,916
She said she'd come see her...

311
00:16:16,916 --> 00:16:18,850
once things settled down
after paying off some of the debt.

312
00:16:18,983 --> 00:16:21,583
Unbelievable. Are divorce...

313
00:16:21,583 --> 00:16:23,483
and paying off debt even comparable?

314
00:16:25,150 --> 00:16:28,250
These are the custody transfer papers.

315
00:16:28,250 --> 00:16:29,583
She asked me to give them to Eun Hyeong...

316
00:16:30,350 --> 00:16:31,550
so he can file them with the court.

317
00:16:39,950 --> 00:16:41,850
She says they've already agreed on it.

318
00:16:43,450 --> 00:16:44,783
What on earth is going on?

319
00:16:47,583 --> 00:16:50,383
I'll give them to Eun Hyeong.
You stay out of it.

320
00:16:54,883 --> 00:16:56,883
Since I work during the day
and go home at night,

321
00:16:57,250 --> 00:16:59,450
I kind of feel like a model citizen now.

322
00:16:59,450 --> 00:17:01,650
I'm actually proud of myself.

323
00:17:02,550 --> 00:17:03,950
A model citizen? That's a bit much.

324
00:17:04,583 --> 00:17:06,250
Weren't you like that before?

325
00:17:06,783 --> 00:17:09,450
Honestly, when staying up all night
became my routine,

326
00:17:09,883 --> 00:17:12,283
I'd go home during the day and doze off,

327
00:17:13,750 --> 00:17:16,383
and sometimes I'd wonder if I was a loser.

328
00:17:17,250 --> 00:17:19,950
But thanks to you, I feel like
I've gotten my healthy routine back.

329
00:17:20,650 --> 00:17:21,650
Thank you.

330
00:17:22,750 --> 00:17:24,250
It's nothing.

331
00:17:27,483 --> 00:17:28,550
My babies.

332
00:17:29,250 --> 00:17:31,650
Sleep well, Bung Nim. Good night.

333
00:17:32,050 --> 00:17:33,950
By the way,

334
00:17:33,950 --> 00:17:36,050
why does only one of them have a name?

335
00:17:36,350 --> 00:17:37,650
Won't the nameless one feel left out?

336
00:17:39,050 --> 00:17:40,583
I couldn't think of anything suitable.

337
00:17:41,450 --> 00:17:43,850
Then should I name that one?

338
00:17:45,950 --> 00:17:47,050
Do you have something in mind?

339
00:17:47,650 --> 00:17:49,950
Yes. How about Bung Wu?

340
00:17:50,950 --> 00:17:52,083
What? Bung Wu?

341
00:17:52,683 --> 00:17:55,583
Then is that one me?

342
00:17:55,950 --> 00:17:56,950
What's wrong?

343
00:17:59,850 --> 00:18:02,050
That one's Bung Nim,
so this one can be Bung Wu.

344
00:18:02,583 --> 00:18:04,883
Should we just give them surnames too?

345
00:18:05,050 --> 00:18:06,050
Cho Bung Nim and Seo Bung Wu?

346
00:18:06,183 --> 00:18:08,783
What? So they're supposed to be us now?

347
00:18:13,650 --> 00:18:14,650
Hello, Oh Hye Ji.

348
00:18:16,950 --> 00:18:19,983
Really? Okay, then I'll go there.

349
00:18:21,483 --> 00:18:23,650
Oh Hye Ji wants to have dinner.
Want to come?

350
00:18:23,650 --> 00:18:24,650
Are you crazy?

351
00:18:25,350 --> 00:18:26,850
Why would I tag along?

352
00:18:26,983 --> 00:18:29,783
Tag along? Oh Hye Ji is your friend.

353
00:18:30,050 --> 00:18:31,550
That makes me the one tagging along.

354
00:18:32,050 --> 00:18:34,283
Go hear it from Hye Ji yourself.

355
00:18:34,583 --> 00:18:36,583
What happened that night.

356
00:18:37,550 --> 00:18:38,550
That night?

357
00:18:39,150 --> 00:18:40,650
That night?

358
00:18:41,583 --> 00:18:43,550
What is she talking about?

359
00:18:46,450 --> 00:18:47,950
Bung Nim and Bung Wu,

360
00:18:48,350 --> 00:18:50,250
don't fight all night, and be nice.

361
00:18:51,850 --> 00:18:52,983
Wait for me!

362
00:18:54,783 --> 00:18:55,850
Where are you going this late?

363
00:18:55,950 --> 00:18:59,183
I left some urgent documents
at the office. Go to sleep first.

364
00:19:01,350 --> 00:19:03,150
What's gotten into him?

365
00:19:04,150 --> 00:19:05,750
He barely touched his food.

366
00:19:07,750 --> 00:19:09,150
Something's definitely strange.

367
00:19:23,350 --> 00:19:24,083
(Office café, noon, Jeong Dong Pal)

368
00:19:24,083 --> 00:19:25,350
Jeong Dong Pal?

369
00:19:26,283 --> 00:19:28,750
"Wednesday, noon, office café."

370
00:19:31,283 --> 00:19:32,350
That man from before?

371
00:19:49,850 --> 00:19:51,850
What is it? How did you find me here?

372
00:19:53,783 --> 00:19:57,783
You blew me off the moment we met,

373
00:19:58,750 --> 00:20:00,950
so I hired a private investigator.

374
00:20:02,250 --> 00:20:04,650
You're the one
who'd been desperately looking for me.

375
00:20:05,750 --> 00:20:06,783
I figured...

376
00:20:07,950 --> 00:20:10,350
I'd have to come to your house
if necessary.

377
00:20:11,783 --> 00:20:15,283
I only recently found out that
Chairman Ko Kang Su of Kangsu Group...

378
00:20:16,650 --> 00:20:20,583
was Site Manager Ko Kang Su
from 50 years ago.

379
00:20:23,250 --> 00:20:26,683
Actually,
I got out of prison just a month ago.

380
00:20:27,450 --> 00:20:29,250
Life's hard,

381
00:20:29,883 --> 00:20:31,750
so I kept ending up back inside.

382
00:20:33,083 --> 00:20:36,083
I've got five stars.

383
00:20:37,750 --> 00:20:40,650
I'll let you know the time
and place tomorrow, so please leave.

384
00:20:42,050 --> 00:20:44,350
That woman who remarried
Site Manager Ko Kang Su...

385
00:20:45,183 --> 00:20:46,783
I barely remember her name.

386
00:20:49,050 --> 00:20:50,450
You're looking for her daughter,
aren't you?

387
00:20:55,650 --> 00:20:57,883
You're the Chief Assistant
of Kangsu Group,

388
00:20:58,983 --> 00:21:00,950
and you live in an apartment like this.

389
00:21:02,883 --> 00:21:03,883
You've done well for yourself.

390
00:21:06,150 --> 00:21:07,150
Right, 4885?

391
00:21:16,650 --> 00:21:19,850
Let's meet somewhere quiet tomorrow.

392
00:21:21,683 --> 00:21:25,450
I have a lot to tell you.

393
00:21:27,683 --> 00:21:30,883
You need to find Yeon Sun, don't you?

394
00:21:57,450 --> 00:21:59,150
Hey, Seung Ri. Just getting home?

395
00:21:59,750 --> 00:22:00,750
Yes, Dad.

396
00:22:01,650 --> 00:22:02,850
Why are you outside?

397
00:22:03,350 --> 00:22:06,383
I was just getting some fresh air.

398
00:22:07,183 --> 00:22:08,183
Let's go in.

399
00:22:08,550 --> 00:22:09,850
- Okay.
- Let's go.

400
00:22:20,650 --> 00:22:22,550
- I'm home.
- Welcome back.

401
00:22:23,650 --> 00:22:27,183
I thought you went to the office.
Why are you back already?

402
00:22:27,850 --> 00:22:31,383
I realized it could wait until tomorrow.

403
00:22:32,483 --> 00:22:33,950
Seung Ri, it's late. Go get some rest.

404
00:22:34,583 --> 00:22:36,083
Okay. Good night.

405
00:22:37,983 --> 00:22:41,350
Honey, go to bed first.
I need to work a little longer.

406
00:22:42,750 --> 00:22:44,983
All right. Don't stay up too late.

407
00:22:53,650 --> 00:22:54,650
Who is he?

408
00:22:57,250 --> 00:22:58,983
It's definitely that old man from before.

409
00:23:00,450 --> 00:23:02,150
Why do I have such a bad feeling
about this?

410
00:23:13,250 --> 00:23:14,250
You're not sleeping?

411
00:23:14,483 --> 00:23:16,550
What? I was about to.

412
00:23:17,983 --> 00:23:20,683
Then why haven't you changed clothes,

413
00:23:20,683 --> 00:23:21,850
and why do you keep looking at the clock?

414
00:23:22,350 --> 00:23:23,483
No, I didn't.

415
00:23:25,283 --> 00:23:27,050
I think I need some fresh air.

416
00:23:27,483 --> 00:23:29,350
My head's pounding after meetings all day.

417
00:23:29,750 --> 00:23:31,850
Just admit
you're going to see Team Manager Ko.

418
00:23:32,150 --> 00:23:34,083
Do you think I'm that clueless?

419
00:23:34,350 --> 00:23:37,650
Why are you so quick to notice everything?

420
00:23:38,550 --> 00:23:39,550
I'll be back soon.

421
00:23:40,050 --> 00:23:41,450
You don't have to.

422
00:23:42,050 --> 00:23:44,050
Whoever falls asleep first gets the bed.

423
00:23:44,350 --> 00:23:45,550
Fine.

424
00:23:52,750 --> 00:23:55,350
Why are you so late?
It's been five minutes.

425
00:23:55,850 --> 00:23:57,183
I had to make sure Eun Nim
wasn't suspicious.

426
00:23:58,050 --> 00:23:59,683
What's all this?

427
00:24:00,683 --> 00:24:01,983
We have something to do tonight,

428
00:24:02,550 --> 00:24:04,483
so I needed the basic setup ready.

429
00:24:04,750 --> 00:24:05,750
What?

430
00:24:05,750 --> 00:24:06,983
The waltz we learned before.

431
00:24:07,150 --> 00:24:09,083
We haven't practiced once since then.

432
00:24:09,850 --> 00:24:11,250
It took so much effort to learn.
It'd be a waste.

433
00:24:11,450 --> 00:24:14,783
So you want to practice waltzing here?

434
00:24:14,950 --> 00:24:17,150
Why not? Everyone's asleep.

435
00:24:17,450 --> 00:24:18,950
Let's do just three rounds and go inside.

436
00:24:19,550 --> 00:24:21,650
What if the music wakes everyone up?

437
00:24:22,250 --> 00:24:23,983
Don't worry. Believe it or not,

438
00:24:24,950 --> 00:24:26,250
I'm a strategist.

439
00:24:27,383 --> 00:24:30,050
You're seriously suggesting we waltz here?

440
00:24:31,550 --> 00:24:32,550
Unbelievable.

441
00:24:32,950 --> 00:24:33,950
All right.

442
00:24:39,683 --> 00:24:40,750
- Can you hear it?
- Yes.

443
00:25:11,550 --> 00:25:12,550
Eun Hyeong.

444
00:25:13,150 --> 00:25:14,150
Big bro.

445
00:25:14,250 --> 00:25:17,150
Little bro, Cho Eun Ae.

446
00:25:17,783 --> 00:25:21,350
The reason we're out here is...

447
00:25:22,050 --> 00:25:24,183
Actually,
for the second round of the competition,

448
00:25:24,183 --> 00:25:26,850
we're adding
a cultural experience program...

449
00:25:27,483 --> 00:25:30,450
Please come inside. I'll explain calmly.

450
00:25:32,450 --> 00:25:33,850
And what's with your outfit?

451
00:25:40,550 --> 00:25:44,150
So the woman you're in love with...

452
00:25:45,250 --> 00:25:46,250
is Eun Ae?

453
00:25:48,750 --> 00:25:51,383
I never would've imagined that.

454
00:25:53,183 --> 00:25:55,850
I'm sorry I didn't tell you sooner.

455
00:25:56,683 --> 00:25:59,750
You already had enough on your mind,
so I didn't want to add to it.

456
00:26:01,950 --> 00:26:04,750
Our family recently made a promise.

457
00:26:05,550 --> 00:26:07,250
No keeping secrets from each other.

458
00:26:07,883 --> 00:26:09,983
No carrying burdens alone.

459
00:26:10,550 --> 00:26:13,750
Whether good or bad,
we share everything together.

460
00:26:14,250 --> 00:26:16,883
- Then that means I'm...
- Yes.

461
00:26:18,150 --> 00:26:20,983
You're family too now,
so I hope you'll follow that promise.

462
00:26:21,583 --> 00:26:23,950
You're accepting me as family too?

463
00:26:24,150 --> 00:26:25,150
Of course.

464
00:26:25,783 --> 00:26:29,050
This is how I see it.
Family isn't just about blood.

465
00:26:29,983 --> 00:26:31,750
We live together under one roof every day,

466
00:26:32,050 --> 00:26:35,450
eat together, share beds, share worries...

467
00:26:36,050 --> 00:26:37,883
And now you're dating Eun Ae.

468
00:26:38,350 --> 00:26:39,750
If that's not family, what is?

469
00:26:40,883 --> 00:26:41,883
Big bro.

470
00:26:43,283 --> 00:26:46,650
My sister, Cho Eun Ae,
is truly a wonderful person.

471
00:26:47,150 --> 00:26:48,150
Please take good care of her.

472
00:26:48,983 --> 00:26:50,050
You have my word.

473
00:26:50,050 --> 00:26:53,183
I'll do my best to love Eun Ae well.

474
00:26:53,250 --> 00:26:54,350
Of course you will.

475
00:26:55,450 --> 00:26:57,250
I don't know about anything else,

476
00:26:57,850 --> 00:26:59,850
but if you ever make Eun Ae cry,

477
00:27:02,250 --> 00:27:03,250
I won't let it slide.

478
00:27:05,383 --> 00:27:07,083
Yes, I'll remember that.

479
00:27:09,050 --> 00:27:10,083
You two look great together.

480
00:27:55,350 --> 00:27:56,350
What's this?

481
00:27:56,783 --> 00:27:58,183
Did Grandma post this?

482
00:28:02,250 --> 00:28:03,150
(Registered Missing Person Details)

483
00:28:03,150 --> 00:28:04,783
(Adopted in France in 1977,
Adoption annulled in 1981)

484
00:28:04,783 --> 00:28:06,550
(Last known location,
a diner at Anhui-dong)

485
00:28:07,950 --> 00:28:10,750
What is going on?

486
00:28:11,650 --> 00:28:12,750
This necklace...

487
00:28:27,150 --> 00:28:28,950
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
